DATA CLOUD
Segment Types and Statuses

Learn more about the values provided about each segment. View details in the Segments section of Data Cloud, or in Publish History for a specific segment. Depending on how you create the segment, the type can be UI (created via the Segment Builder), Lookalike (created via a seed segment), or DBT (created via the API).

Segment Status

The Segment Status field provides details about your segment. If you don’t get an updated status and population count after saving the segment or after a couple of minutes, click the dropdown menu and select Update Status.

SEGMENT STATUS	DEFINITION
Active	Segment created and all segment functionality available
Processing	Publishing segment in progress
Recounting	Recounting the segment population in progress
Error	Segment is active but can’t be manually published
Inactive	Segment can only be deleted
Publish Status

The Publish Status field provides details on the segment’s publishing status to the activation target.

PUBLISH STATUS	DEFINITION
Success	Segment published successfully to the activation target
Error	Segment failed to publish, contact Salesforce Customer Support for help
Skipped	Publishing the segment is temporarily delayed for 30 minutes due to the maximum number of segments publishing simultaneously
Publishing	Publishing segment in progress, segment data from last publish is available until publishing is complete
Blank (No Status)	Segment was created but not published
Deferred	Segment publish time is pushed out due to exceeding the maximum number of simultaneous publishes
Publish Schedule

The Publish Schedule determines when and how often your segment publishes to an activation target.

IMPORTANT Make sure all segments with a preset publish schedule also have an activation. Segments require a publish schedule and an activation to be sent to an activation target.
PUBLISH SCHEDULE	DEFINITION
Don’t refresh	Segment not published to activation targets
1 hour	Segment published every hour (Marketing Cloud Engagement only)
4 hours	Segment published every 4 hours (Marketing Cloud Engagement only)
12 hours	Segment published every 12 hours
24 hours	Segment published every 24 hours
Next Publish Date Time

The Next Publish Date Time for a segment is an estimate and can change depending upon concurrency limits and how many segments are in progress for publishing. A manual segment publish takes priority over a scheduled publish.

Publish Type

Segments are either published on a schedule using the Publish Schedule or manually by clicking Publish Now for a segment.

PUBLISH TYPE	DEFINITION
Scheduled	
Segment was published using a standard schedule of every 12 or 24 hours
Segment was published using a rapid segment schedule of every 1 or 4 hours (Marketing Cloud Engagement only)

Manual	Segment was published on demand by clicking Publish Now for the segment
Platform

The Platform column provides details about the activation target where the segment was published.

PLATFORM	DEFINITION
CC	Segment published to a B2C Commerce activation target
Ecosystem	Segment published to an External Activation Platform activation target
Interaction Studio	Segment published to a Marketing Cloud Personalization (formerly Interaction Studio) activation target
Loyalty	Segment published to a Data Cloud activation target
SFMC	Segment published to a Marketing Cloud Engagement activation target
S3	Segment published to a Cloud File Storage (Amazon S3) activation target
